This building was so fire damaged it was deemed unsafe to enter. We were called in to carry out an aerial photogrammetry survey to asses the extent of damage for insurance and planning purposes.  We also carried out a topographical survey to create a 3D model of the building in order to provide the client and stakeholders with a more stimulating visual representation of the site. Additional outputs included scalable 2D orthomosaics and elevation models. We can get our accuracies down to just 20mm for measurements.

Visual inspection inside one of the chimneys at the iconic London landmark, the Battersea Power Station today. Requires high levels of concentration and skill in a very tight operating zone. One of the few drone companies to have permission granted to fly at the power station.
